Why ResNet50 is a Good Choice for Waste Classification

Architectural Advantages:

 - Residual connections prevent vanishing gradients, enabling effective training of deep networks

 - Bottleneck design (1×1 convolutions) reduces computational cost while maintaining representational power

 - 2048-dimensional feature vector captures both low-level (texture, edges) and high-level (shape, composition) features

 - Critical for distinguishing visually similar waste materials (plastic vs. paper, glass vs. clear plastic)


Transfer Learning Suitability:

 - Pretrained on ImageNet-1K (1.2M images, 1000 classes)

 - Pretraining includes objects with textures similar to waste (bottles, cans, cardboard, bags)

 - Provides strong foundation for fine-grained waste classification tasks


====================================== Implementation Justification =============================================================
Pretrained Weights:

 - IMAGENET1K_V2 used instead of V1

 - Improved accuracy on downstream tasks

 - Better feature representations for transfer learning


Freezing Mechanism:

 - freeze=True enables two-phase training strategy

 - Phase 1: Train only classifier head (10-20 epochs, higher LR)

 - Phase 2: Unfreeze backbone for fine-tuning (20-50 epochs, lower LR)

 - Prevents destruction of pretrained features during initial training

 - Essential when working with moderate-sized waste datasets


Classification Head Design:

 - Progressive compression: 2048 → 512 → 28

 - Intermediate 512-dim layer learns task-specific feature combinations

 - Prevents overfitting compared to direct 2048 → 28 mapping


Dropout Strategy:

 - Dropout 0.4 on first linear layer → strong regularization

 - Dropout 0.2 on second linear layer → lighter regularization before final classification

 - Prevents over-reliance on specific features

 - Improves generalization to real-world waste images


Parameter Counting Methods:

 - Enables model efficiency comparison across architectures

 - Total parameters: ~25.6M

 - Trainable parameters adjustable via freeze/unfreeze

================= Training Strategy =====================================
Two-Phase Approach:

Phase 1
	Backbone: Frozen
	Adapts classifier to waste classification
	Learning rate is 1e-3 to 1e-4
	Epochs 10-20
	
Phase 2
	Backbone: Unfrozen
	Fine-tune for waste-specific features
	Learning rate is 1e-5 to 1e-6
	Epochs 20-50

Rationale:
Phase 1: Leverages ImageNet features while learning waste-specific decision boundaries

Phase 2: Gradually adjusts backbone features for waste domain without catastrophic forgetting

